Russian Equity Movers: Magnit, Surgutneftegas Shares Are Active

-- B y   M a r i a   L e v i t o v   a n d   K i r a   S a v c e n k o
-- 
2011-08-11T16:03:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/russian-equity-movers-polymetal-magnit-novatek-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 0.5
percent to 1,438.91 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index lost 0.5 percent to 1,544.83.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Magnit (MGNT RX),  Russia ’s biggest food retailer by
market value, dropped 5.9 percent to 3,115.30 rubles, the lowest
since September 2010, after the Federal Statistics Service said
the country’s economic growth slowed for a second quarter,
missing the median estimate by economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  OAO Surgutneftegas (SNGS RX), a Russian oil producer, slid
3.6 percent to 21.991 rubles, the weakest in two years, after
oil traded as low as $81.03 a barrel today. That compares with
an average price of $97.62 a barrel this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
